Model Structure Analysis Token Analysis Type Subset Analysis

Overview of concepts

name (freq: 101) - Full name
given-name (freq: 998) - First name
additional-name (freq: 7) - Middle name (middle initial in case of max-length=1)
family-name (freq: 995) - Last name
 
address - Address of a physical location - Artificial concept, not to be used in HTML
street-address (freq: 36) - Street address (house number, street name, apartment)
address-line1 (freq: 1136) - 1st line of street-address
address-line2 (freq: 1137) - 2nd line of street-address
address-line3 (freq: 19) - 3rd line of street-address
address-line4 - 4th line of street-address
locality1 (freq: 1132) - City
admin-area1 (freq: 1007) - State
postal-code (freq: 1208) - Postal code
postal-code-prefix - Postal code prefix
postal-code-suffix - Postal code suffix
country (freq: 589) - 2-letter country code
country-name - Name of a country (e.g. "USA")
 
organization (freq: 253) - Name of an organization/company
 
credit-card - Artificial concept, not to be used in HTML
cc-name (freq: 307) - Full name of credit card holder
cc-given-name (freq: 21) - Given name of credit card holder
cc-additional-name - Additional name of credit card holder
cc-family-name (freq: 21) - Family name of credit card holder
cc-number (freq: 649) - Credit card number
cc-exp-MMYY (freq: 362) - Credit card expiration date in format MM/YY
cc-exp-MM (freq: 254) - Credit card expiration month (2 digits)
cc-exp-YY (freq: 52) - Credit card expiration date in format YY (2 digits)
cc-exp-MMYYYY (freq: 10) - Credit card expiration date in format MM/YYYY
cc-exp-MM (freq: 254) - Credit card expiration month (2 digits)
cc-exp-YYYY (freq: 206) - Credit card expiration date in format YYYY (4 digits)
cc-csc (freq: 627) - CSC/CVC/CVV number
cc-type (freq: 15) - Credit card type
 
tel (freq: 42) - Full telephone number
tel-country-code (freq: 22) - Country code component of the telephone number
tel-national (freq: 816) - Telephone number without the county code component, with a country-internal prefix applied if applicable
tel-area-code (freq: 2) - Area code component of the telephone number, with a country-internal prefix applied if applicable
tel-local - Telephone number without the country code and area code components
tel-local-prefix (freq: 5) - First part of the component of the telephone number that follows the area code, when that component is split into two components
tel-local-suffix (freq: 5) - Second part of the component of the telephone number that follows the area code, when that component is split into two components
tel-extension (freq: 33) - Telephone number internal extension code
 
email (freq: 459) - Email address
